result.execSummary:
The defendant Erica R. Swartz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Penalty - Retail Theft (<=$500)], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Statement as to Negotiated Plea and Diversion Agreement

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Poss.  Plead no contest to 2 counts (Counts 1 and 3) of retail theft, as a Class A Misdemeanor.  Amended information filed,  adding count 3.  Count 2 dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.  Court recited the charge and the possible penalties.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defense stipulated as to a factual basis for the plea.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights. Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of amended Counts 1 and 3.  943.509(1m)(b).   Joint recommendation for  2 years probation.  Conditions recommended:  no contact with Walmart. 75 hrs of community service due within the first 6 months of probation.  Seek and maintain employment.    Not to possess or consume any controlled substances.   Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Not to possess any prescription medications of any kind unless those have been prescribed to the defendant by a physician, and in that case, the defendant shall take such medications only as prescribed.  Defendant shall not alter the form of any prescription prior to, or in conjunction with, ingestion.  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Defendant exercised her right to allocution.  

Court ordered:  sentence withheld, 2 years probation. Concurrent No contact with Black River Falls Walmart.  Pay restitution.  To be determined.     Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants.
